ettings.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Disable &#x201C;Anyone can register.&#x201D;<\/li><li>Set your site language<\/li><li>Set the correct time\/date format.<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#x2019;s say you <strong>start a travel blog<\/strong> named &#x201C;Bangkok food is great&#x201D; and attach this to the category <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/thailand\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Thailand (opens in a new tab)\">Thailand<\/a>. WordPress by default creates an URL like: <br>http:\/\/yourtravelblogname.com\/?p=400<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/start-a-travel-blog-header.jpg\" alt=\"start a travel blog settings\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"310\" alt=\"start a travel blog settings\" class=\"wp-image-9490 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-300x206.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-600x413.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-450x310.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-800x550.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-1080x743.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-30x21.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-163x112.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-262x180.jpg 262w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-768x528.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-1024x705.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-1440x991.jpg 1440w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header-30x21.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/07\/23151000\/start-a-travel-blog-header.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>Let&#x2019;s change this markup so Google can read this URL. In the WordPress admin; navigate to Settings -&gt; Permalinks. Select the custom structure in the permalink screen and fill in:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>\/%category%\/%postname%\/<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n\n<p>It will create the following URL format:&#xA0;<br>&#x2018;http:\/\/yourtravelblogname.com\/thailand\/bangkok-food-is-great&#x2019;. <br>This format is much better for readability and search engines. (SEO)<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>See:<\/strong> <a class=\"anchor\" href=\"#masterclass\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Masterclass blogging<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div><\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"layout\">5. Get a layout for your travel blog<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two flavors to go with when you start picking a travel blog layout. You either:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Create your own unique template by hiring a developer.<\/li><li>Buy one from a WordPress themes webshop. (<a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/go\/elegant-themes\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Like this one (opens in a new tab)\">Like this one<\/a>)<\/li><\/ol>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>The second option is cheaper but has its limitations; Someone else could have the same layout for their blog and themes are not optimized to help a travel blog score in Google (SEO).<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--readmore \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--readmore\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>A look inside:<\/strong> Our <a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/tips\/camera-travel-photography\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Travel Photography Camera (opens in a new tab)\">Travel Photography Camera<\/a> Bag<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscrip